    "author_association": "NONE",
    "body": "### Problem\n\nWhen opening a file inside a tarball and checking the current directory with `:pwd`, is something like `/private/var/folders/kb/g4jdr8294rb53jn01hhtxv880000gn/T/nvim/_ZIPVIM_`, rather than the current directory set by the user.\n\nAttempting to write to the file gives this error:\n\n```\nError detected while processing BufWriteCmd Autocommands for \"tarfile::*\"..function tar#Write:\nline  128:\nE344: Can't find directory \"/var/folders/kb/g4jdr8294rb53jn01hhtxv880000gn/T/nvim.username/pKkJue/1\" in cdpath\nE472: Command failed\n```\n\n### Steps to reproduce\n\n```bash\ntouch foo\ntar cf foo.tar foo\nnvim --clean foo.tar\n```\n- open the foo file inside the archive\n- check `:pwd` output\n- `:write` to the file\n\n### Expected behavior\n\n- pwd should be not changed to the __ZIPVIM__ directory\n- writing to the file should not raise the error\n\n### Nvim version (nvim -v)\n\nNVIM v0.11.1 Build type: Release LuaJIT 2.1.1744318430\n\n### Vim (not Nvim) behaves the same?\n\nyes, 9.1.1350\n\nrelated vim issue: https://github.com/vim/vim/issues/17334\n\n### Operating system/version\n\nmacOS 15.5 (Sequoia)\n\n### Terminal name/version\n\nalacritty\n\n### $TERM environment variable\n\ntmux-256color\n\n### Installation\n\nBrew",
